						<summary>

						<p>CHIDAMBARAM, CHIDAMBARAM TALUK, SOUTH ARCOT DISTRICT.</p>						

						<p>Naṭarāja temple, west <hi rend="italic">gōpuram.</hi> right of entrance.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Māṟan.</hi></p>						

						<p>The middle portion is very much damaged. The beginning six lines and the last five lines are also damaged. The record is in Tamil verses, the first of which compares Māṟan with Lord Kṛishṇa in the baby form lying on the pipal leaf. There is a reference to Podimuṉivaṉ in the latter portion, which seems to be the same name as Podiyil-muṉivaṉ, sage Agastya.</p>						

						</summary>
